title: CANBERRA'S MINIATURE FLOOD TWO BRIDGES SUBMERGED BY RIVER HEAVY RAIN DISORGANISES TELEPHONE SYSTEM REASSURING REPORTS OF RIVER FALLING  Heavy rain in the catchment areas of the Molonglo and Queanbeyan Rivers caused a swift rise in the river at Canberra in the early hours of yesterday morning, and the river in many places wat running level with the banks yesterday afternoon. Early in the day the flood waters overwhelmed the bridges at Scott's Crossing and Acton, and the city transport services were temporarily disorganised. Re-assuring messages were received yesterday afternoon from the Commission's flood patrol service at points on the upper reaches of both rivers, indicating that the waters were falling. Owing to water entering the telephone cable t[?]ns, serious disorganisation of the city telephone service was occasioned yesterday, and 800 telephone lines wete affected.
